nd on the way American social policy has evolved and compares the situation in the U.S. to the social policies and ideologies of other countries.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aSingle motherszUnited StatesxEconomic conditions. 0aSingle motherszUnited StatesxSocial conditions. 0aWelfare recipientszUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aamerica.  aamerican dream.  achildrearing.  aclass differences.  adivorce.  aemotional.  afamily relationships.  agender studies.  ahistorical analysis.  amodern motherhood.  amoms.  amotherhood.  anonfiction.  anontraditional families.  aparenthood.  apolitical analysis.  apolitics of parenthood.  araising children.  aseparation.  asingle motherhood.  asingle mothers.  asingle parenting.  asocial classes.  asocial policies.  asociological perspective.  asociologists.  aunited states.  awidows.  awomen.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093957840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520939578423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520939578/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles